/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 5055 m
gs 1 -1 sc (1. A sampe, x\(n\), arrives.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 5295 m
gs 1 -1 sc (2. A pointer to an FIR filter is selected from the Filter Pointer Ring as indexed by theCommutator Index.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 5535 m
gs 1 -1 sc (3. The sample, x\(n\) is sent to the FIR filter via the pointer access.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 5775 m
gs 1 -1 sc (4.  The FIR filter performs the convolution operation and sends its output to the summer.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 6015 m
gs 1 -1 sc (5. The summer adds the output value of the FIR filter to its current value.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 6255 m
gs 1 -1 sc (6.The commutator index is decremented by one.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 6495 m
gs 1 -1 sc (7, Steps 1 through 6 are repeated as each new sample, x\(n\) arrives until commutator index is equal to -1.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 6735 m
gs 1 -1 sc (8. IF comutator index is equal to -1.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 6975 m
gs 1 -1 sc (8.1 Comutator index is set back to M-1 \(wrap around\).) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 7215 m
gs 1 -1 sc (8.2 Summer contents are written to storage supplied by the caller.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 7455 m
gs 1 -1 sc (8.2 The summer is cleared for the next commutator cycle.) col0 sh gr
/Times-Roman-iso ff 180.00 scf sf
495 7695 m
gs 1 -1 sc (9. The cycle repeats for the next M samples of x\(n\).) col0 sh gr
